On Fri, 24 Jan 2003, Jon DeVos wrote:

> Listees, how long should it take someone who knows what he/she is doing
> to replace the head gaskets on my '78 bus?  Thanks!  Beth

There are no "head gaskets" in a stock '78 bus engine.  There may/may not
be a set of copper seals between the heads and cylinders depending on who
built the engine, but they don't serve the same purpose as a traditional
head gasket.

What problem is trying to be solved?

